  "25": {
    "Unknown": "And, agreeably to this figure of speech, the voice of the LORD is upon the waters of the sanctuary, causing them to give life, and to call into spiritual life sinners which were before dead in trespasses and in sins. It was by this voice of JEHOVAH, light sprung forth at the original creation of nature. It is the same almighty, quickening, life-giving power, when GOD, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, shineth in the heart, whereby he giveth the light of the knowledge of the glory of [v_2Co_4_6] GOD, in the face of JESUS CHRIST; 2 Corinthians 4:\n25. And what an awful visitation soon after followed upon Jerusalem. LORD! how slow soever may seem to some men the just judgment of GOD, yet it doth not [v_2Pe_2_3] slumber. 2 Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]` 2:"
  },
